vectorData.altText: Note how bridges over the sulci (grooves) and other irregularities on the surface of the brain.
Can you identify all the numbered structures and spaces? Click here for the answer:
USING the whole brain at your station, examine the arachnoid mater.

Note the presence of vessels deep to the arachnoid matter, these are cerebral arteries and veins.
What is the name of the space deep to the arachnoid mater that contains cerebral arteries and veins?
What fluid fills this space? 
What is the name given to the accumulation of blood in this space with rupture of a cerebral artery? 
The pia mater is closely adhered to the surface of the brain and cannot be pulled away without damaging the underlying brain tissue.
